2013.assessment:
No foreign military forces based in Malaysia. The Lahad Datu incursion by
Sulu sultanate forces from Philippines was repelled by Malaysian armed forces;
this was not a foreign military occupation but an armed intrusion.

2024.assessment:
CL score 4. Continued Partly Free status. Civil liberties environment stable
under Anwar government. Some positive developments in media access;
ongoing concerns about religious freedom and LGBTQ+ restrictions.

2012.assessment:
No armed conflict. BERSIH 3.0 (April 2012) drew over 100,000 protesters;
police response included some violence but no fatalities. Malaysia remained
free of organized armed political violence.

2018.assessment:
Interpolated estimate of 48 for 2018 (regime change year). Post-May 2018:
PH government revealed full extent of government liabilities including 1MDB;
this transparency revelation was significant though not captured in OBS score.

Statistical capacity 84 in regime change year. DOSM is an independent agency;
statistical production unaffected by political transition. Post-election,
PH government made fiscal statistics more transparent by disclosing 1MDB liabilities.
